               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-2v: Image of Mary (an unusual form, Image of the flower?).  F<locus target="#3r">3r, </locus>-34r: Canticle of the Flower, arranged by a later hand for the days of the week. F<locus target="#35r">35r, </locus>-47v: Lamentation of the Virgin. F<locus target="#49r">49r, </locus>-54v: Unidentified asmat prayer. F<locus target="#55r">55r, </locus>-63r:  Unidentified asmat prayer, mentioning the story of the True Cross.   F<locus target="#63v">63v, </locus>-73v:  Unidentified asmat prayer. F<locus target="#83r">83r, </locus>-87v: Asmat prayer which Jesus gave to his disciples on Dabra Zait. F<locus target="#88r">88r, </locus>-94v: Asmat of Christ. F<locus target="#95r">95r, </locus>-102r: Asmat Prayer for Remission of Faith of the Disciples. F<locus target="#102v">102v, </locus>-109v: Asmat prayer that was given to the three Hebrew children. F<locus target="#111r">111r, </locus>-119v: Image of the Savior of the World. F<locus target="#34r">34r, </locus> and 47v mention the owner, Walda Iyasus Danachaw. <locus target="#119v">119v, </locus>: mentions the scribe, Walda Rufa'el. <locus target="#119v">119v, </locus>: record: completion of the book: dated 1918 EC in the year of Saint Mark, Nahase 3. <locus target="#120r">120r, </locus>: record, written in blue ink, of the sale of property. Buyer and seller are mentioned. Illuminations (verfy high quality): F. ii r(ecto) Madonna and Child, flanked by two angels holding a canopy over them. <locus target="#34v">34v, </locus>: Madonna and Child under a vine with leaves, aged man with cave to the right, soldier with spear in upper right. <locus target="#48v">48v, </locus>: God the Father, enthroned, surrounded by the four living creatures.  <locus target="#110v">110v</locus>: Crucifixion of Jesus Christ. </summary>
